---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import merinoSweaterImage from "../assets/sweater.webp";
const title = "The Sartorial Economist";
---
<Layout title={title} description="Your guide to the best clothing you can buy.">
  <p class="text-center text-gray-600 italic">Your guide to the best clothing money can buy</p>
  <p class="mt-4">This site takes a microeconomic approach to clothing. It identifies items that give you the best "bang for your buck", or in microeconomic terms that maximize the utility per dollar spent. It also includes a detailed analysis of each item's value as well as styling ideas. Peruse the articles below to become as stylish as possible.</p> 
  <p>Each article also includes:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
    <li>Detailed information on what makes the item valuable</li>
    <li>Recommendations for when, how, and why to wear it</li>
    <li>Outfit ideas</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Explore the articles below to build a wardrobe you'll love wearing.</p>

  <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl border p-4 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 items-center text-center sm:text-left sm:items-start">
    <Image
        src={merinoSweaterImage}
        alt="Everlane Merino Sweater"
        class="w-32 h-auto rounded-md object-cover"
    />
    <div class="sm:ml-4">
      <a href="/everlane-merino-sweater" class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-700 hover:underline">
        The Best Spring Base Layer
      </a>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Everlane's Merino Crew Neck is a temperature-regulating stapleâ€”see why it's your best spring investment.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>
